Hormonal acne 
Your hormones fluctuate throughout your  cycle and this  can trigger your sebaceous glands to secrete more sebum and too much sebum can result clogged pores and breakouts.
The solution to this is that you should  keep your pores clear especially around  this time of the month . 
For that you can use a salicylic acid based face wash ( do a patch test before using ) . , use a BHA toner to regulate oil production 
And you can also use tea tree oil based products to kill the acne producing bacteria .

Grapefruit 
Grapefruit contains a good amount of Vitamin A and C. It is rich in minerals, antioxidants and has high water content. It keeps your skin’s outer layer hydrated. Vitamin C and antioxidants protect the skin from environmental hazards. Stimulates production of skin collagen which makes skin smooth, plump and increases  its elasticity .

‘Breakfast nutrition’ for glowing skin 
🍃Sprouts 
Sprouts are high in antioxidants and Vitamin C that  fight cell damaging free radicals and  promote a clear and firmer skin through the production of collagen. 

🍃Almonds 
The star vitamin of almonds that is Vitamin E helps to keep lines and wrinkles at bay .
They also help reduce acne by increasing the levels of antioxidants and selenium in the body.

🍃Pomegranate contains about 48% of the daily vitamin C, and  other antioxidants which help to  block free radical damage , that further helps to reduce the signs of ageing. 
It is rich in tannins, anthocyanins, and ellagic acid, all of which reverse free radical damage
Pomegranates help boost circulation, which in turn boosts your skin cell turnover. This allows for quicker tissue repair and allows for faster wound healing.
